<p>Update on what happened across the GNOME project in the week from May 10 to May 17.</p>
<h1 id="sovereign-tech-fund">
<a class="heading-anchor" href="#sovereign-tech-fund" hidden><svg width="16" height="16"><use xlink:href="https://thisweek.gnome.org/images/icons.svg#anchor"></use></svg></a>Sovereign Tech Fund
</h1><p><a href="https://matrix.to/#/@tbernard:gnome.org">Tobias Bernard</a> reports</p>
<blockquote>
<p>As part of the <a href="https://foundation.gnome.org/2023/11/09/gnome-recognized-as-public-interest-infrastructure">GNOME STF (Sovereign Tech Fund)</a> initiative, a number of community members are working on infrastructure related projects.</p>
<p>Here are the highlights for the last week:</p>
<p>Alice <a href="https://gitlab.gnome.org/GNOME/gtk/-/merge_requests/6540">landed CSS variables in GTK</a> ðŸ¥³</p>
<p>Alice also <a href="https://gitlab.gnome.org/GNOME/libadwaita/-/merge_requests/1099">ported</a> libadwaita to the new CSS variables, <a href="https://gitlab.gnome.org/GNOME/libadwaita/-/merge_requests/1111">added &ndash;window-radius</a>, <a href="https://gitlab.gnome.org/GNOME/libadwaita/-/merge_requests/1103">synced AdwComboRow with GTK changes</a>, added a <a href="https://gitlab.gnome.org/GNOME/libadwaita/-/merge_requests/1109">default Adw(Application)Window size</a>, fixed some <a href="https://gitlab.gnome.org/GNOME/libadwaita/-/merge_requests/1114">dialog focus bugs</a> and improved <a href="https://gitlab.gnome.org/GNOME/libadwaita/-/merge_requests/1115">alert dialog styles</a> in addition to various other bug fixes, refactors, and reviews.</p>
<p>Adrian is working on a new installer for GNOME OS. It&rsquo;s still very early days though, so there isn&rsquo;t a repo yet.</p>
<p>Felix started investigating how to allow <a href="https://github.com/bilelmoussaoui/oo7/issues/94">changing passwords of secret-service collections</a>.</p>
<p>Sam worked on the addressing the open questions with the <a href="https://gitlab.gnome.org/Teams/Design/app-mockups/-/commit/9be6fad519cac79728ed4662d91059e87000a06e">file chooser designs</a>.</p>
<p>Antonio continued work on the Nautilus file chooser, includign some <a href="https://gitlab.gnome.org/GNOME/nautilus/-/work_items/3431">refactoring</a> to minimize code duplication between Nautilus and file chooser and <a href="https://gitlab.gnome.org/GNOME/nautilus/-/commit/c09c6184000c988fb13712b5a6e77f909c3074ef">implementing an adaptive file chooser layout</a> following the latest mockups.</p>
<video controls preload="auto" width="100%"  playsinline class="html-video">
    <source src="https://thisweek.gnome.org/posts/2024/05/twig-148/81aa9a62315bccdd50c00111812fd577eba1a5331791570662410682368.webm" type="video/webm">
  <span>Your browser doesn't support embedded videos, but don't worry, you can <a href="https://thisweek.gnome.org/posts/2024/05/twig-148/81aa9a62315bccdd50c00111812fd577eba1a5331791570662410682368.webm">download it</a> and watch it with your favorite video player!</span>
</video>
<p>Dorota continued working on the global shortcuts portal, creating a <a href="https://gitlab.gnome.org/dcz/gsimpl">prototype portal implementation for testing</a>, finishing the <a href="https://gitlab.gnome.org/GNOME/gnome-control-center/-/merge_requests/2485">GNOME Settings side of the portal</a> (waiting for maintainer feedback), and <a href="https://gitlab.gnome.org/GNOME/mutter/-/merge_requests/3680#note_2107354">addressing feedback to the mutter MR</a>.</p>
<p>Joanie worked on various regression fixes and cleanups in Orca.</p>
<p>Matt worked on text support in the <a href="https://gitlab.gnome.org/mwcampbell/gtk/tree/accesskit">GTK AccessKit implementation</a>. The implementation now supports GtkLabel, GtkInscription, and GtkText-based editable widgets (e.g. GtkEntry), including complex cases like bidirectional text and combining characters (e.g. some emoji). The implementation is now complete enough to support full screen reader access to single-line editable widgets. He also added passive key snooping to Newton&rsquo;s AT client protocol (involving <a href="https://gitlab.gnome.org/mwcampbell/mutter/tree/newton-prototype-2">mutter</a>, <a href="https://gitlab.gnome.org/mwcampbell/newton_consumer">newton_consumer</a>, <a href="https://gitlab.gnome.org/mwcampbell/newton_atspi_compat">newton_atspi_compat</a>, and <a href="https://gitlab.gnome.org/mwcampbell/orca/tree/newton">Orca</a>), and fixed a number of bugs across the stack to get to the point of being able to record a working demo of the whole Newton stack with the GNOME Podcasts app.</p>
<video controls preload="auto" width="100%"  playsinline class="html-video">
    <source src="https://thisweek.gnome.org/posts/2024/05/twig-148/newton-demo-2024-05-17.mp4" type="video/mp4">
